    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[175ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[225ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-and-ginger-buffalo-double-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice-and-slaw/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chicken</strong> to a clean chopping board, cover with <strong>cling film </strong>and bash with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until flattened to approx. 1cm thickness</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-and-ginger-buffalo-double-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice-and-slaw/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high-heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>flattened chicken</strong> and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-and-ginger-buffalo-double-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice-and-slaw/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Rinse your <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-and-ginger-buffalo-double-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice-and-slaw/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>grated carrot </strong>and <strong>rinsed edamame </strong>with your <strong>mayo </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!) in a bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>carrot & edamame slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-and-ginger-buffalo-double-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice-and-slaw/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong> to a heatproof bowl and put in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 20 secs or until melted</p><p>Once melted, add your <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>ginger paste</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>sriracha</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and the <strong>remaining rice vinegar </strong>to the bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Stir it all together<strong> </strong>\u2013<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>honey & ginger buffalo sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-and-ginger-buffalo-double-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice-and-slaw/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, add the <strong>honey & ginger buffalo sauce </strong>and cook for 1 min or until all coated \u2013 this is your <strong>honey & ginger buffalo chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-and-ginger-buffalo-double-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice-and-slaw/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>cooked chicken</strong> thinly on a clean board</p><p>Serve the <strong>sliced double chicken </strong>with the <strong>cooked cauliflower rice</strong> and <strong>carrot & edamame slaw </strong>to the side</p><p>Spoon over the <strong>honey & ginger buffalo sauce</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
